2. Ordered;
and proved at Court
An Inventory to be taken & with the Will Recorded. That such Wills and Testaments be Exhibited to be proved by the Executor or Executors, at the next County Court after the Death of the Testator, if it may be: and that a true Inventory of the Estate duely valued be presented to be Sworn to, and left to be Recorded with the Will; and the Probate shall not be taken until such Inventory is presented, or sufficient Bond given for the speedy performance of the same.
